The '''Talaud kingfisher''' ('''''Todiramphus enigma''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Alcedinidae]].

It is [[endemic]] to the [[Talaud Islands]] north of [[Sulawesi]] in [[Indonesia]].

Its natural [[habitat]]s are [[Subtropics|subtropical]] or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s and [[river]]s.
It is threatened by [[habitat loss]], but as of 2016, the [[Population (biology)|population]] was considered stable.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Talaud Kingfisher |url=https://www.iucnredlist.org/species/22683410/92986201 |website=IUCN RedList}}</ref>

